        "to": "Dead Letter Topic (payment.events.dlq)",
        "status": "risk",
        "issue": "DLQ exists but its effectiveness is undermined by the early offset commit. If the process crashes between offset commit and exhausting retries, the event never reaches the DLQ either — it simply vanishes. Additionally, no DLQ consumer or alerting on DLQ depth was mentioned."
      }
    ],
    "contract_compliance": "Event schema contract between Kafka producer and this consumer is not described. Deserialization failures should be handled explicitly and routed to DLQ rather than crashing the consumer loop.",
    "data_flow_integrity": "BROKEN. The commit-before-process pattern creates an at-most-once delivery guarantee. For payment events, at-least-once is the minimum acceptable guarantee. Events can be silently lost on any crash, restart, deployment, or OOM kill between offset commit and processing completion."
